{#- §04 SETUP PROTOCOL (4-phase HowTo → process-grid) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="setup-protocol" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§04</span><span class="idx__t">The TechBrot Setup Protocol</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:12px;">Every setup engagement runs four phases.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 44px;max-width:60ch;">Four phases, each with a named output &mdash; so you always know what you&rsquo;re getting and when.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in protocol %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n{% if loop.last %} process-step__n--done{% endif %}">{{ s.num }}{% if loop.last %} &check;{% endif %}</div><h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3><p class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 0 8px;">{{ s.when | safe }}</p><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p style="margin-top:8px;"><strong>Output:</strong> {{ s.output | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §05 DELIVERABLES (included + configured checklists) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="setup-deliverables">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§05</span><span class="idx__t">The deliverables</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:20ch;margin-bottom:36px;">What you actually get from a setup engagement.</h2>
    <div class="r-2" style="gap:24px;">
      <div class="incl-card">
        <h3>Every setup includes</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for d in included %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
      </div>
      <div class="incl-card">
        <h3>Configured when scope requires</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for d in configured %}<li>{{ d | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §06 PRODUCTS (which QuickBooks product — 6 buyer cards → lift) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="setup-products" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§06</span><span class="idx__t">Product selection</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:22ch;margin-bottom:36px;">Which QuickBooks product fits your business.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for p in products %}
      <div class="lift"><span class="lift__n">{{ p.tag | safe }}</span><div><h3>{{ p.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ p.body | safe }}</p></div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- §07 FOUNDATION (what setup is for — 3 prose paras, bespoke; not a spine block) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="setup-foundation">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§07</span><span class="idx__t">What setup is actually for</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:24px;">Setup is the foundation. The relationship is what comes next.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The strict technical work of QuickBooks setup &mdash; chart of accounts, opening balances, integrations &mdash; takes 2 to 4 weeks. The reason it matters runs longer than that.</p>
      <p>A well-built QuickBooks file is the foundation everything else depends on. Monthly bookkeeping runs cleanly because the file was built right. Tax preparation takes hours instead of days because your CPA isn&rsquo;t fixing structural problems first. Financial advisory work &mdash; cash-flow forecasting, margin analysis, scenario planning, fractional CFO engagement &mdash; only works on top of accurate books.</p>
      <p>Most TechBrot setup engagements continue into monthly bookkeeping with the same operator. Many continue further &mdash; into multi-state sales-tax compliance, payroll management, and, as the business grows, the advisory work that distinguishes a profitable operation from a struggling one. The setup is the first decision in a longer relationship. We build the file accordingly.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
